Given a 2D array (matrix), the task is to calculate the sum of all the elements present in the matrix.

Input Format

The first line contains the size of the matrix N (number of rows) and M (number of columns).

The next N lines contain M integers each, representing the matrix.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

The output prints a single integer, the sum of all elements in the matrix.

Sample Input 0

3 3
1 2 3
4 5 6
7 8 9
Sample Output 0

Sum of Matrix : 45


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
       int r=sc.nextInt();
       int c=sc.nextInt();
       int arr[][]=new int[r][c];
       for(int i=0;i<r;i++)
       {
        for(int j=0;j<c;j++)
        {
            arr[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
        }
       }
       int sum=0;
       for(int i=0;i<r;i++)
       {
        for(int j=0;j<c;j++)
        {
            sum+=arr[i][j];
        }
       }
       System.out.print("Sum of Matrix : "+sum);
    }
}
